Sentencas: Deformation of the interconnect in a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) stack affects the internal thermal stresses of the cell at high temperatures.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation

Sentencas: In this study, the effect of the interconnect deformation on the cell temperature and thermal stress at different operating voltages was simulated based on the thermal-chemical-electrical-mechanical multiphysics coupling theory.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation

Sentencas: The results show that when the operating voltage of the cell is above 0.85 V, the interconnect mainly generates a compressive strain.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation

Sentencas: When the operating voltage is below 0.85 V, the interconnect produces tensile strain, which increases with decreasing voltage.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation

Sentencas: Interconnect deformation significantly increases the thermal stress of the cells within the stack, but effectively improves the uniform distribution of thermal stress.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation

Sentencas: The coupling effect of interconnect deformation on cell thermal stress within the stack varies at different operating voltages.
Titulo: Thermal Stress Analysis of a Solid Oxide Fuel Cell Considering Interconnect Deformation
